react-a11y-dialog is a thin React layer on top of [a11y-dialog](/projects/a11y-dialog/). It wraps the same accessibility behaviour in idiomatic React: a component API, a hook for imperative control, and props that map cleanly to dialog state.

## When to use it

Reach for it when you are already on React and want a battle-tested dialog implementation, with proper ARIA wiring and open/close lifecycle without re‑implementing those details yourself.

If you can use the native `<dialog>` element and it fits your browser support matrix, that is often simpler today but this package remains useful where you need the older pattern or tighter control.

## API surface

The repository documents both the component and hook exports, TypeScript types, and how to forward refs or render into portals. Head to GitHub for install instructions and examples.
